Class Structure

java.lang.Object
  com.daohoangson.uml.structures.Structure
All Implemented Interfaces:
StructureListener
Direct Known Subclasses:
Argument, Class, Interface, Method, Property
public abstract class Structure
extends java.lang.Object
implements StructureListener

A very basic structure. It has all the required methods but no direct instance can be created

Version:
1.3
Author:
Dao Hoang Son

cfg_container_structures

protected java.lang.String[] cfg_container_structures
Specifies if the structure accepts container. Each structure can only accept 1 container! Default value is empty string which means doesn't accept container. A non-null structure name means accept a container with the specified structure name.

cfg_parent_structures

protected java.lang.String[] cfg_parent_structures
Specifies if the structure accepts parents. Each structure can accept many container! Default value is empty string which means doesn't accept parents. A non-null structure name means accept parents with the specified structure name.

cfg_child_structures

protected java.lang.String[] cfg_child_structures
Specifies if the structure accepts children.

cfg_hide_visibility

Specifies if the structure wants to hide visibility

cfg_hide_children

Specifies if the structure wants to manage children by itself.

cfg_regex_name

protected java.lang.String cfg_regex_name
The Regular Expression used match against name string. Subclass can set to null value to skip checking for match. Name must not begin with number. Name can only contain alphabetic characters and numbers.

See Also:
setName(String)

cfg_regex_type

protected java.lang.String cfg_regex_type
The Regular Expression used to match against type string. Subclass can set to null value to skip checking for match. Supports generalize types. Supports arrays. Primary type: group 1.
Generalized: group 3.

See Also:
setType(String)
